'''''Kelvaquenta''''' (composed of the [[Quenya]] words ''[[kelvar]]'' + ''[[quenta]]'') was the journal of the Linguistic Fellowship of [[Cleveland Tolkien Society]]. The journal was a continuation of the ''Cleveland Tolkien Society Newsletter'' (numbering uninterrupted). Vol. 1, no. 3 (Oct. 1977) - Vol. 1, no. 5 (Spring 1978) are kept in the [[Marquette University|J.R.R. Tolkien Collection at the Marquette Archives]].<ref>{{webcite|author=Russell A. Potter|articleurl=http://rapsvault.blogspot.com/2013/08/kelvaquenta.html|articlename=Kelvaquenta|dated=7 August 2013|website=[http://rapsvault.blogspot.com/ From the Vaults of RAP]|accessed=23 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{webcite|articleurl=http://www.tolkienguide.com/modules/wiwimod/index.php?page=Kelvaquenta|articlename=Kelvaquenta|dated=20 October 2006|website=Guide|accessed=23 October 2014}}</ref>
